Equivocal (2+) - Complete membrane staining that is either non-uniform||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|67|  or weak intensity but with obvious circumferential distribution in at||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|68|  least 10% of invasive cells, or intense complete membrane staining in||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|69|  30% or less of tumor cells.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|70|  Negative (0 or 1+) - No staining or weak incomplete membrane staining in||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|71|  any proportion of invasive tumor cells, or weak, complete membrane||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|72|  staining in less than 10% of tumor cells.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|73|  ||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|74|  Equivocal Category for HER2 IHC results: A HER2, 2+ staining result that||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|75|  is interpreted as equivocal may not indicate gene amplification.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|76|  ||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|77|  A FISH test for HER2 gene amplification is ordered for all HER2 IHC 2+||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|78|  results.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|79|  ||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|80|  Methodology||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|81|  ||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|82|  ER/PR:||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|83|  Fixation Type and Length: Tissue was fixed in 10% neutral buffered||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|84|  formalin (Cardinal Health McGaw Park IL, Cat.C4320-105) for a minimum of||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|85|  at least 6 hours and not longer than 72 hours.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|86|  Antibody and Assay Methodology: Estrogen receptor alpha (clones 6F11)||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|87|  and Progesterone receptor (clone 312), Leica Microsystems, Newcastle||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|88|  Upon Tyne, UK).||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|89| These control slides||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|91|  run along side of this patient's sample showed appropriate staining.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|92|  Specimen Adequacy: The patient's tissue was adequate for evaluation.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|93|  ||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|94|  HER2:||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|95|  Fixation Type and Length: Tissue was fixed in 10% neutral buffered||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|96|  formalin (Cardinal Health McGaw Park IL, Cat.C4320-105) for a minimum of||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|97|  at least 6 hours and not longer than 72 hours.||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|98|  Antibody and Assay Methodology: Rabbit monoclonal anti-human HER2, clone||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|99|  4B5, (FDA-approved), (Ventana Medical Systems, Tucson, AZ).||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|100|  Control Slides Examined: External kit-slides provided by manufacturer||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|101|  (cell lines with high, low and negative HER2 protein expression), and||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|102|  in-house known HER2 amplified control tissue were evaluated along with||||||FOBX||TX|APRESULT^.|103|  the test tissue.
